f(x)=x-2 \sin x 
f'(x)=1-2 \cos x 
f''(x)=2\sin x
f'(x)=0
x=1.047
 0 = f'(x) = 1 - 2\cos(x) 
 \cos(x) = \frac{1}{2}. 
x \in [0 , 2\pi]
f'(x) = 1 - 2\cos x = 0 \implies \cos x = \dfrac 12 \implies x = \pi/3 \;\text{or}\; x  = 5\pi /3
x = \pm \frac \pi 3 + 2\pi n, \; n \in \mathbb Z
x = \pi/3, \;2\sin x = 2 \sin\left(\frac \pi 3\right) = \sqrt 3 > 0
x = \frac {5\pi}{3},\;\; 2\sin x = 2 \sin\left(\frac{5\pi}3\right) = -\sqrt 3 < 0
x = \pi/3 + 2\pi n > 0 \implies f''(x) > 0,\quad x = -\pi/3 + 2\pi n \implies f''(x) < 0, \quad n\in \mathbb N
